awards-2016-complete-winners-list |archivedate=24 May 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Brit Awards]]\n|[[Brit Award for British Album of the Year|British Album of the Year]]\n|{{Won}}\n|rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"McGeorge 2016\"/>\n|-\n| [[Danish Music Awards]]\n| International Album of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>https://genius.com/Danish-music-awards-de-nominerede-2016-lyrics</ref>\n|-\n| [[Echo Music Prize|ECHO Music Awards]]\n| Album of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=10 March 2016 |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/adele-tops-noms-germany-s-874167 |title=Adele Tops Noms for Germany's Echo Music Awards |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=10 March 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160311110014/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/adele-tops-noms-germany-s-874167 |archivedate=11 March 2016 }}</ref><br/><ref>{{cite news|accessdate=8 April 2016 |url=http://www.echopop.de/fileadmin/echopop/upload/news/2016/PM_8_ECHO_2016_Gewinner.pdf |title=ECHO 2016: Vier Preise f\u00fcr Helene Fischer |work=ECHO Deutsche Musikpreis |date=7 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413133053/http://www.echopop.de/fileadmin/echopop/upload/news/2016/PM_8_ECHO_2016_Gewinner.pdf |archivedate=13 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Album of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/taylor-swift-the-weeknd-lead-iheartradio-music-awards-noms-20160209 |title=Taylor Swift, the Weeknd Lead iHeartRadio Music Awards Noms |work=Rolling Stone |date=9 February 2016 |accessdate=10 February 2016 |author=Blistein, Jon |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160210093249/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/taylor-swift-the-weeknd-lead-iheartradio-music-awards-noms-20160209 |archivedate=10 February 2016}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web |url=https://news.iheart.com/features/iheartradio-music-awards-15/articles/15/490103/surprise-announcement-adele-accepts-song-of-14552999/ |title=Surprise Announcement! Adele Accepts Song Of The Year iHeartRadio Music Award In The Middle Of Her Concert |publisher=[[iHeartMedia]] |date=31 March 2016 |accessdate=31 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406072716/http://news.iheart.com/features/iheartradio-music-awards-15/articles/15/490103/surprise-announcement-adele-accepts-song-of-14552999/ |archivedate=6 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Juno Awards]]\n|[[Juno Award for International Album of the Year|International Album of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"1\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://junoawards.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/2016-Gala-Dinners-Awards-Winners-List.pdf |title=2016 JUNO Gala Dinner & Awards Winners |work=JUNO Awards |date=3 April 2016 |accessdate=3 April 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415101905/http://junoawards.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/2016-Gala-Dinners-Awards-Winners-List.pdf |archivedate=15 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Los Premios 40 Principales]]\n| [[Premios 40 Principales for Best International Album|International Album of the Year]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2016/nominados/ |title=LOS40 Music Awards 2016: Nominados |language=Spanish |publisher=[[Los 40 Principales]] |date=6 October 2016 |accessdate=11 October 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011231149/http://los40.com/especiales/los40-music-awards/2016/nominados/ |archivedate=11 October 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| [[iHeartRadio Music Awards]]\n| Best Pop Album\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=1|<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.iheart.com/news/heres-the-complete-list-of-iheartradio-15616268/ |first=Isha |last=Thorpe |publisher=iHeartMedia |title=Here's The Complete List Of #iHeartAwards Winners |date=5 March 2017 |accessdate=5 March 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170409080744/https://www.iheart.com/news/heres-the-complete-list-of-iheartradio-15616268/ |archivedate=9 April 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|[[Grammy Awards]]\n| [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|accessdate=6 December 2016 |url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees |title=59TH ANNUAL GRAMMY AWARDS NOMINEES |work=The Recording Academy |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180131073014/https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/59th-annual-grammy-awards |archivedate= 31 January 2018 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album|Best Pop Vocal Album]]\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n== Commercial performance ==\n\n=== Europe ===\nIn the United Kingdom, ''25'' debuted at number one on the [[UK Albums Chart]] and sold 800,307 copies in its first chart week, overtaking [[Oasis (band)|Oasis]]' ''[[Be Here Now (album)|Be Here Now]]'' (1997) to become the [[List of fastest-selling albums|fastest-selling album]] of all time in the UK.<ref name=\"OCC week 1\">{{cite news|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-s-25-is-officially-the-uk-s-biggest-selling-number-1-album-ever__12416/|title=Adele's 25 is officially the UK's biggest selling Number 1 album ever|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=27 November 2015|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=27 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116092558/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-s-25-is-officially-the-uk-s-biggest-selling-number-1-album-ever__12416/ |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> Of that total, 252,423 copies were digital downloads, breaking the record for most digital copies sold in a week, and 548,000 were physical copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Sets Biggest U.K. Opening Sales Week, Most Downloaded No. 1 Album|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6777865/adele-25-sets-biggest-uk-opening-sales-week-most-downloaded-no-1-xl-recordings-official-charts-company|website=Billboard|accessdate=27 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211014137/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6777865/adele-25-sets-biggest-uk-opening-sales-week-most-downloaded-no-1-xl-recordings-official-charts-company |archivedate=11 December 2018}}</ref> In its first week, ''25'' sold more copies in the UK than the combined sales of the last 19 number-one albums in UK on their debut week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34948022|title=Adele's 25 makes UK chart history with 800,000 album sales|work=BBC News |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011115004/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34948022 |archivedate=11 October 2018}}</ref> It also outsold that week's other 86 highest-selling albums combined.<ref name=\"OCC week 1\" /> After ten days on sale, it became the fastest million-seller in the UK, surpassing ''Be Here Now'', which achieved this feat in 17 days in 1997.<ref name=\"1 million in UK\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/overnight-news-from-around-the-world-89/063519|title=Adele's 25 enters record books for fastest million seller in the UK|work=Music Week|date=30 November 2015|first=Tom|last=Pakinkis|accessdate=30 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116112748/http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/overnight-news-from-around-the-world-89/063519 |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In its second week, ''25'' sold 439,337 copies, which broke the record for highest second-week sales in the UK and also was the sixth biggest weekly sales of all time.<ref name=\"uksales2ndweek\">{{cite news|url=http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/adele-breaks-uk-record-for-biggest-second-week-album-sales/063579|title=Adele breaks UK record for biggest second week album sales|last=Jones|first=Alan|date=4 December 2015|work=[[Music Week]]|accessdate=4 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116115242/http://www.musicweek.com/news/read/adele-breaks-uk-record-for-biggest-second-week-album-sales/063579 |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In its third week, ''25'' sold 354,000 copies, which represents the second highest third-week sales since [[Take That]]'s ''[[The Circus (Take That album)|The Circus]]'', which sold 382,000 copies in its third week,<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele beats Coldplay to Number 1 on the Official Albums Chart|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adeles-25-beats-coldplays-a-head-full-of-dreams-to-number-1-on-the-official-albums-chart__13161/|publisher=officialcharts.com|accessdate=11 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306190106/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adeles-25-beats-coldplays-a-head-full-of-dreams-to-number-1-on-the-official-albums-chart__13161/ |archivedate=6 March 2019}}</ref> and was also certified quintuple platinum by the [[British Phonographic Industry]], with total UK sales at 1,593,530 copies.<ref name=\"third week sales\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicweek.com/businessanalysis/read/official-charts-analysis-adele-beats-coldplay/063634|title=Official Charts Analysis: Adele beats Coldplay|last=Jones|first=Alan|date=11 December 2015|work=[[Music Week]]|accessdate=11 December 2015|url-access=subscription  }}{{dead link|date=July 2019|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> On 18 December 29 days after its release, the album surpassed sales of 2 million copies in the UK, becoming the fastest 2 million-seller in the country.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-s-25-becomes-the-fastest-2-million-selling-album-in-uk-chart-history__13224/|title=Adele's 25 becomes the fastest 2 million-selling album in UK chart history|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=18 December 2015|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=18 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116100101/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-s-25-becomes-the-fastest-2-million-selling-album-in-uk-chart-history__13224/ |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In its fifth week of release, the album sold another 450,000 copies in the UK, becoming the Christmas number one.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele scores the biggest selling album of Christmas 2015|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-scores-the-biggest-selling-album-of-christmas-2015__13261/|publisher=Official Charts Company|accessdate=25 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116090507/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-scores-the-biggest-selling-album-of-christmas-2015__13261/ |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> The album has spent 13 non-consecutive weeks at number one<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-says-hello-to-number-1-again-after-headlining-glastonbury__15539/|title=Adele says Hello to Number 1 again after headlining Glastonbury|last=Myers|first=Justin|date=1 July 2016|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=2 July 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116090651/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adele-says-hello-to-number-1-again-after-headlining-glastonbury__15539/ |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> and, as of November 2016, had sold 3.12 million copies, being later certified 11\u00d7 Platinum.<ref name=\"bpi\" /><ref name=\"November UK sales\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adeles-25-one-year-on__17207/|title=Adele's 25 one year on: 14 incredible chart facts|last=Myers|first=Justin|date=26 November 2016|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=26 November 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116095931/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/adeles-25-one-year-on__17207/ |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In December 2016, it became only the third album to be the UK's biggest-seller two years in a row, after [[Simon & Garfunkel]]'s ''[[Bridge over Troubled Water]]'' (1970 and 1971) and [[Simply Red]]'s ''[[Stars (Simply Red album)|Stars]]'' (1991 and 1992).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/official-charts-analysis-little-mix-return-to-albums-summit/067017|title=Official Charts Analysis: Little Mix return to albums summit|last=Jones|first=Alan|date=30 December 2016|work=[[Music Week]]|accessdate=30 December 2016|url-access=subscription  |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116113342/http://www.musicweek.com/analysis/read/official-charts-analysis-little-mix-return-to-albums-summit/067017 |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> It has sold over 3.50&nbsp;million copies as of October 2018, making the ten biggest selling studio album in the UK history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-uks-biggest-studio-albums-of-all-time__24431/|title=The UK's biggest studio albums of all time|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=13 October 2018|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=13 October 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107091751/https://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-uks-biggest-studio-albums-of-all-time__24431/ |archivedate=7 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nElsewhere in Europe, ''25'' also opened atop of the German charts after selling 263,000 units, the largest weekly sale for a record since [[Herbert Gr\u00f6nemeyer]]'s 2007 release ''[[12 (Herbert Gr\u00f6nemeyer album)|12]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Neues Album \"25\": Adele gelingt das Triple in Deutschland|url=http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/musik/adele-und-25-bester-albumstart-in-deutschland-seit-acht-jahren-a-1064966.html|work=Der Spiegel|accessdate=27 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171118104018/http://www.spiegel.de/kultur/musik/adele-und-25-bester-albumstart-in-deutschland-seit-acht-jahren-a-1064966.html |archivedate=18 November 2017}}</ref> In France, ''25'' became the fastest-selling album of 2015 after it sold 169,693 copies, of which 26,295 were downloads.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele : \"25\" num\u00e9ro un des ventes en France. Un d\u00e9marrage spectaculaire !|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/Adele/news-99911.html|website=Charts in France|accessdate=27 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813111432/http://www.chartsinfrance.net/Adele/news-99911.html |archivedate=13 August 2018}}</ref> The album sold another 129,200 copies in France in its second week, bringing its two-week total to 300,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Albums : Adele r\u00e9siste remarquablement, Fr\u00e9ro Delavega plus fort que Patrick Bruel|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/actualite/news-100097.html|publisher=chartsinfrance.net|accessdate=8 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116055349/http://www.chartsinfrance.net/actualite/news-100097.html |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In its third week, ''25''<nowiki/>'s sales rose to 132,200 copies in France, bringing its total sales to 430,000 copies, which made it the third best-selling album of the year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Albums : Adele toujours loin devant, Jul \u00e9crase Coldplay, Booba et Rohff|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/actualite/news-100191.html|publisher=chartsinfrance.net|accessdate=16 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116055317/http://www.chartsinfrance.net/actualite/news-100191.html |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In its fourth week of sales in France, sales of the album further rose to 133,000 copies, bringing its total sales to 565,000 copies in the country, earning it a diamond certification there.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chartsinfrance.net/Adele/news-100280.html|title=Charts in France |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813112428/http://www.chartsinfrance.net/Adele/news-100280.html |archivedate=13 August 2018}}</ref> In the Netherlands, the album debuted at number one with first week sales of over 120,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele verslaat Marco Borsato in Album Top 100|url=http://megatop50.3fm.nl/nieuws/detail/349843/adele-verslaat-marco-borsato-in-album-top-100|website=Mega Top 50|accessdate=29 November 2015 }}{{dead link|date=July 2019|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> The album also sold over 180,000 copies in the [[Benelux]] in its first week of release.<ref>{{cite web|title=Industrie levert 200.000 fysieke cd's Adele en Marco Borsato uit {{!}} Nieuws {{!}} Entertainment Business|url = http://www.entertainmentbusiness.nl/nieuws/2015-W47/industrie-levert-200000-fysieke-cds-adele-marco-borsato-uit|website = www.entertainmentbusiness.nl|accessdate = 5 December 2015 }}</ref> In Spain, the album debuted atop the charts selling 20,000 copies in its first week,<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele agota entradas para sus dos conciertos en Barcelona \u2013 20minutos.es|url=http://www.20minutos.es/noticia/2620203/0/adele-concierto-barcelona/entradas-agotadas/nueva-fecha/|website=20minutos.es \u2013 \u00daltimas Noticias|accessdate=5 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116032541/https://www.20minutos.es/noticia/2620203/0/adele-concierto-barcelona/entradas-agotadas/nueva-fecha/ |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> while in Portugal it also debuted at number one with sales of 3,200 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele: 25 vendeu 3 mil e 200 c\u00f3pias na primeira semana em Portugal|url=https://blitz.sapo.pt/adele-i25i-vendeu-3-mil-e-200-copias-na-primeira-semana-em-portugal=f98803|website=BLITZ|accessdate=5 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190318171329/https://blitz.pt/principal/update/adele-i25i-vendeu-3-mil-e-200-copias-na-primeira-semana-em-portugal=f98803 |archivedate=18 March 2019}}</ref> ''25'' also entered the charts at number one in Switzerland, selling over 40,000 copies in its first week, receiving a double platinum certification there.<ref>{{cite web|title=20 Minuten \u2013 Adele nimmt Kurs auf Schweizer Allzeitrekord \u2013 Musik|url=http://www.20min.ch/entertainment/musik/story/Adele-nimmt-Kurs-auf-Schweizer-Allzeitrekord-25623986|website=20 Minuten|accessdate=5 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180813111736/https://www.20min.ch/entertainment/musik/story/Adele-nimmt-Kurs-auf-Schweizer-Allzeitrekord-25623986 |archivedate=13 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== North America ===\nIn the United States, ''25'' sold 2.3 million after three days of availability, becoming the fastest-selling album of the 21st century and the best-selling album of 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6770443/adeles-25-two-million-first-three-days|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Adele's '25' Sells 2.3 Million in First Three Days in U.S., Aiming for 2.9 Million Debut Week|work=Billboard|date=23 November 2015|accessdate=23 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308082435/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6770443/adeles-25-two-million-first-three-days |archivedate=8 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6770470/adele-25-already-2015-biggest-selling-album|title=Adele's '25' Is Already 2015's Biggest-Selling Album|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=23 November 2015|work=Billboard|accessdate=24 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190302210428/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6770470/adele-25-already-2015-biggest-selling-album |archivedate=2 March 2019}}</ref> The album reached sales of 2.433 million early on its fourth day, surpassing the single-week record for an album since [[Nielsen Soundscan]] began tracking sales in 1991, set by [[NSYNC]]'s ''[[No Strings Attached (NSYNC album)|No Strings Attached]]'' in March 2000 when it debuted with 2.416 million copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official: Adele Breaks *NSYNC's Single-Week U.S. Album Sales Record|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6776941/adele-breaks-album-sales-record-single-week-nsync|website=Billboard|accessdate=24 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224190907/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6776941/adele-breaks-album-sales-record-single-week-nsync |archivedate=24 December 2018}}</ref> In total, it sold 3.38 million copies in the US in its first week, becoming the first album ever to sell over 3 million copies in a week.<ref name=\"usdebut\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6777905/adele-25-sales-first-week-us|title=Adele's '25' Official First Week U.S. Sales: 3.38 Million|work=Billboard|date=28 November 2015|accessdate=28 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127071838/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6777905/adele-25-sales-first-week-us |archivedate=27 November 2018}}</ref> The album earned 3.48 million [[album-equivalent unit]]s in the US in its first week of release, which is the largest registered figure since the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] began tracking weekly popularity based on overall units in December 2014. ''25'' also achieved 96,000 in track-equivalent album units in the US in its debut week, and another 8,000 in streaming-equivalent album units, all of which came from streams of the single \"Hello\", as it was the only song from the album available on streaming services.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Debuts at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart, '21' Returns to Top 10|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6777926/adele-25-debuts-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart|website=Billboard|accessdate=29 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118134036/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6777926/adele-25-debuts-no-1-billboard-200-albums-chart |archivedate=18 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn the first three days of its second week, ''25'' sold over 650,000 units, surpassing 4 million sales, ending the week with 1.11 million copies.<ref name=\"us4mil\">{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Sales Rise to Over 4 Million in U.S.|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6778038/adele-25-sales-4-million|website=Billboard|accessdate=1 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181222094603/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6778038/adele-25-sales-4-million |archivedate=22 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Sells 1.11 Million in Second Week in U.S.|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6785931/adele-25-second-week-sales-us|website=Billboard|accessdate=6 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181118101548/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6785931/adele-25-second-week-sales-us |archivedate=18 November 2018}}</ref> In its third full week, the album sold 695,000 copies, surpassing 5 million sales, becoming the first album to do so in a calendar year since Adele's own album ''[[21 (Adele album)|21]]'' in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Hits 5 Million Sold in U.S.|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6805295/adele-25-5-million-sold|website=Billboard|accessdate=10 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190310162817/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6805295/adele-25-5-million-sold |archivedate=10 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Billboard 200: Adele's '25' Rules for Third Week at No. 1, Coldplay Debuts at No. 2 {{!}} Billboard|url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6805727/adeles-25-no-1-on-billboard-200-album-chart-third-week-coldplay-a-head-full-of-dreams|work= Billboard|accessdate = 13 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190305044855/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6805727/adeles-25-no-1-on-billboard-200-album-chart-third-week-coldplay-a-head-full-of-dreams |archivedate=5 March 2019}}</ref> By its fourth week sale of 790,000 copies, ''25'' became the best-selling album in any calendar year since [[Usher (singer)|Usher]] sold 7.98 million in 2004 with ''[[Confessions (Usher album)|Confessions]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Biggest-Selling Album Released Since 2011, Spends Fourth Week at No. 1 |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6813934/adele-25-billboard-200-biggest-selling-album-since-2011 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190305062057/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6813934/adele-25-billboard-200-biggest-selling-album-since-2011 |archivedate=5 March 2019}}</ref> It sold 1.16 million copies in pure album sales in its fifth week, and became the first album to sell over one million copies in three different frames.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Sells Another 1.16 Million in U.S., Spends Fifth Week at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6821619/adele-25-billboard-200-fifth-week-sells-another-million|website=Billboard|date=27 December 2015|accessdate=27 December 2015|author=Caulfield, Keith |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211021152/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6821619/adele-25-billboard-200-fifth-week-sells-another-million |archivedate=11 December 2018}}</ref> In its sixth week, the album sold another 307,000 copies at number one on the ''Billboard'' 200, becoming the first album to sell over 300,000 copies in consecutive six weeks since 2001 when [[Creed (band)|Creed]] did so with ''[[Weathered]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Scores Sixth Week at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6828916/adele-25-sixth-week-no-1-billboard-200|work=Billboard|accessdate=4 January 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181220121218/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6828916/adele-25-sixth-week-no-1-billboard-200 |archivedate=20 December 2018}}</ref> By the end of 2015, ''25'' had sold a total of 8,008,000 equivalent album units, 7,441,000 of which were pure album sales. It also sold 2,310,000 digital copies by the year end, making it the third best-selling digital album of all time behind Adele's own ''21'' and [[Taylor Swift]]'s ''[[1989 (Taylor Swift album)|1989]]''. ''25'' was also the second biggest-selling album of a calendar year by a female artist in Nielsen history, only trailing behind [[Britney Spears]]' ''[[Oops!... I Did It Again (album)|Oops!... I Did It Again]]'' which sold 7,890,000 copies in 2000.<ref name=\"caulfield1\">{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=Adele's '25' Rules as Nielsen Music's Top Album of 2015 in U.S.|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6835248/adele-25-top-album-of-2015-in-us|date=5 January 2016|accessdate=6 January 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820120850/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6835248/adele-25-top-album-of-2015-in-us |archivedate=20 August 2018}}</ref> In its seventh week, the album remained at number one, selling another 164,000 units, becoming the first album by a female artist to top the ''Billboard'' 200 in its first seven weeks since [[Whitney Houston]]'s 1987 album ''[[Whitney (album)|Whitney]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's '25' Still No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart, Rachel Platten Bows in Top Five {{!}} Billboard|url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6836462/adele-25-no-1-billboard-200-rachel-platten-wildfire|website = Billboard|access-date = 11 January 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102205733/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6836462/adele-25-no-1-billboard-200-rachel-platten-wildfire |archivedate=2 January 2019}}</ref> In total, the album has spent ten non-consecutive weeks at the top of the chart, becoming the fifth album released since the 2000 to achieve, at least, 10 weeks at the summit.<ref>{{cite news|first=Keith|last=Caulfield|title=Adele's '25' Scores 10th Week at No. 1 on Billboard 200 Chart|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6890511/adele-25-scores-10th-week-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart|work=Billboard|date=28 February 2016|accessdate=28 February 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211012551/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6890511/adele-25-scores-10th-week-at-no-1-on-billboard-200-chart |archivedate=11 December 2018}}</ref> In the year of 2016, it sold 2.37 million copies and equivalent units, of which 1.7 million were pure sales, ranking as the best-selling album of the year in pure sales and second best including equivalent albums.<ref name=bb2016nielsen>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7647018/drake-views-nielsen-music-top-album-2016-us|last=Caufield|first=Keith|title=Drake's 'Views' Is Nielsen Music's Top Album of 2016 in the U.S.|date=5 January 2017|work=Billboard|accessdate=5 January 2017 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307062847/http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7647018/drake-views-nielsen-music-top-album-2016-us |archivedate=7 March 2019}}</ref> As of March 2018, ''25'' has sold 9.45&nbsp;million copies in pure sales.<ref name=\"ussales\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8257460/taylor-swift-reputation-sells-two-million|title=Taylor Swift's 'Reputation' Becomes Only Album Released in Last Two Years to Sell 2 Million Copies in U.S.|magazine=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=21 March 2018|accessdate=31 May 2018 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181213192713/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8257460/taylor-swift-reputation-sells-two-million |archivedate=13 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn Canada, the album debuted at number one with sales of 306,000 copies, breaking the record for highest first-week sales, which was previously held by [[Celine Dion]]'s ''[[Let's Talk About Love]]'', which had sold 230,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele Becomes First Act Ever To Sell 1&nbsp;m in Two Separate Weeks|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/music-news-adele-becomes-first-act-ever-to-sell-1m-in-two-separate-weeks-20151205|publisher=Noise11.com|accessdate=5 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308080818/http://www.noise11.com/news/music-news-adele-becomes-first-act-ever-to-sell-1m-in-two-separate-weeks-20151205 |archivedate=8 March 2019}}</ref> In its second week ''25'' sold another 145,000 copies in Canada, bringing its two-week total to 451,000 copies. This represents the eighth-highest weekly sales in Canada, as well as the second highest second-week sales for an album, just behind the 146,000 copies sold by the Canadian compilation ''[[Big Shiny Tunes 2]]'' in its second week in 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/67270545/Canadian%20Newsletters/2015/nielsen_music_canadian_update_Dec07_2015.pdf|title=Adele's 25 Reign|accessdate=15 December 2015|publisher=Nielsen SoundScan Canada|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151208125112/https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/67270545/Canadian%20Newsletters/2015/nielsen_music_canadian_update_Dec07_2015.pdf|archive-date = 8 December 2015|url-status = dead}}</ref> The album sold 1 million copies in the nation by May 2016.<ref name=\"cantotal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2016/04/27/adeles-25-has-now-sold-1m-copies-canada|title=Adele's 25 Has Now Sold 1&nbsp;m Copies in Canada|publisher=FYI Music|date=3 May 2016|last=Cross|first=Alan|accessdate=3 May 2016 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830110132/https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2016/04/27/adeles-25-has-now-sold-1m-copies-canada |archivedate=30 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Oceania and South Africa ===\nIn Australia, the album sold more than 210,000 copies in five days, passing the triple platinum mark there.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's 25 hits triple platinum in australia|url=https://www.auspop.com.au/2015/11/adele-25-hits-triple-platinum-in-australia/|website=auspOp|accessdate=25 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190405213043/https://www.auspop.com.au/2015/11/adele-25-hits-triple-platinum-in-australia/ |archivedate=5 April 2019}}</ref> It was the best-selling album of both 2015 and 2016,<ref>{{Cite news|title=Top-selling albums, singles of 2016: Adele is bigger than Christmas|url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/topselling-albums-singles-of-2016-adele-is-bigger-than-christmas-20170105-gtmdhf.html|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|date=6 January 2017|accessdate=30 January 2017 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105203926/https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/topselling-albums-singles-of-2016-adele-is-bigger-than-christmas-20170105-gtmdhf.html |archivedate=5 January 2017}}</ref> and achieved decuple platinum certification (700,000 units) there in May 2017.<ref name=\"auscert\" /> In New Zealand, ''25'' broke the record for highest first week sales, selling 18,766 copies. The previous record holder was [[Susan Boyle]] whose ''[[I Dreamed a Dream (album)|I Dreamed a Dream]]'' sold 17,435 copies in its first week.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Adele breaks NZ record with new album|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11552382|website=The New Zealand Herald|date=27 November 2015|accessdate=29 November 2015|issn=1170-0777 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180719113551/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11552382 |archivedate=19 July 2018}}</ref> By the end of the year, ''25'' became the best-selling album of 2015 in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele's new album storms to top|url=http://m.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11564453|website=The New Zealand Herald|accessdate=21 December 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116112645/https://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=11564453 |archivedate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In South Africa, ''25'' achieved double platinum sales in five days through physical and digital vendors.<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele on fast track with '25'|url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/thetimes/2015/11/25/Adele-on-fast-track-with-25|website=Times LIVE|accessdate=29 November 2015 |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151125212202/http://www.timeslive.co.za/thetimes/2015/11/25/Adele-on-fast-track-with-25 |archivedate=25 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\nIn October 2015, numerous journalists speculated that other musicians had pushed back their albums in order to avoid chart competition with Adele; artists such as [[Justin Bieber]], [[Sam Smith (singer)|Sam Smith]] and [[One Direction]] all did this so that their sales would not be affected.<ref name=\"auto\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/article/34570462/adeles-new-track-other-artists-pushed-material-back-to-avoid-clash|title=Adele's new track: Other artists pushed material back to avoid clash \u2013 BBC Newsbeat|publisher=BBC|date=1 January 1970|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> [[Columbia Records]] shipped 3.6 million physical copies of ''25'', across the United States, making it the most CDs shipped for a new release since the shipment of 2.4 million copies of NSYNC's ''No Strings Attached'' in 2000.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hughes|first=Deirdre|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/adele-s-new-album-may-break--impossible--sales-record-195030302.html|title=Adele's new album may break 'impossible' sales record|work=[[Yahoo!]] Finance|date=19 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> One million copies of ''25'' were shipped to UK retailers, including [[HMV]] and [[Tesco]]. Ian Topping, chief executive of HMV, stated that the company had a great start with the album and sales had exceeded their expectations, continuing to say it was their \"fastest selling album for many years.\"<ref name=\"independent1\">{{cite news|author=Adam Sherwin|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/adele-25-new-album-on-course-to-sell-a-million-copies-on-its-first-day-a6742416.html|title=Adele 25: New album on course to sell a million copies on its first day|work=[[The Independent]]|date=20 November 2015|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the album's release, journalists reported that ''25'' was able to encourage the public to return to buying physical copies, compared to streaming. Adam Shewin of ''[[The Independent]]'' stated that \"''25'' sent casual purchasers back to the remaining physical stores and may even have introduced a new generation to the delights of ownership.\"<ref name=\"independent1\" /> The album was described as saving the music industry, which was seeing dwindling profits with downloading and streaming as the popular methods of music consumption.<ref name=\"indereview\"/> The album was also noted for boosting sales of retailer [[Target Corporation|Target]], which sold the extra track edition of ''25'', during [[Thanksgiving]] and [[Black Friday (shopping)|Black Friday]]. Target Chief Executive Brian Cornell stated that ''25'' was \"the biggest release we've ever had \u2013 this is going to break all the records for us\" and that \"the combination of Adele dropping when it did, the weekend before Thanksgiving, really helped bring in people\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Adele Gives Target a Boost, CEO Says|url=http://fortune.com/2015/11/26/target-adele-black-friday/|website=Fortune|accessdate=27 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe album's first day sales in the US were 1.49 million, averaging at 62,000 copies per hour, and 1,000 copies per minute, while on iTunes, ''25'' sold 900,000 copies on its first day<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2015/12/03/5-statistics-that-highlight-how-amazing-adeles-25-really-is/|title=5 Statistics That Highlight How Amazing Adele's '25' Really Is|work=Forbes|accessdate=22 January 2016}}</ref> becoming the fastest-selling album in iTunes history, breaking the record previously held by [[Beyonc\u00e9]]'s [[Beyonc\u00e9 (album)|self titled]] album.<ref>{{cite news|first=Clarisse|last=Loughrey|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/adeles-album-is-no1-in-almost-every-country-in-the-world-a6749626.html|title=Adele's new album 25 is No.1 on iTunes in almost every country in the world|date=26 November 2015|work=The Independent|accessdate=9 August 2016}}</ref> The album sold more copies in the US in its debut week than the previous number-one albums had sold in the previous 22 weeks combined. Additionally, it sold more copies in its first week than any album sold in an entire calendar year in three recent years (2008, 2009, and 2013).<ref name=\"yahoo.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/music/12-mind-boggling-facts-about-adeles-032640099.html|title=12 Mind-Boggling Facts About Adele's Record-Breaking Debut|date=28 November 2015}}</ref> ''25'' sold more copies in the US in its opening week than the next two best-selling albums of the year combined (Taylor Swift's ''1989'' and [[Drake (rapper)|Drake]]'s ''[[If You're Reading This It's Too Late]]'', which combined to sell 2.885 million copies in 2015).<ref name=\"yahoo.com\" /> ''25'' sold more copies in its first week than the next two fastest-selling albums by female artists combined\u2014[[Britney Spears]]'s ''[[Oops!... I Did It Again (album)|Oops!... I Did It Again]]'', which sold 1.319 million in its first week, and Swift's ''1989'', which sold 1.287 million in its first week.<ref name=\"yahoo.com\" />\n\nIt was stated by ''Billboard'' on 5 January 2016 that in 2015, overall [[album sales]] both digital and physical experienced a 6% decline compared to 2014. ''25'' is credited to having eased the decline of the continuing downfall of album sales. It was also noted that if it was not for the success of ''25'', the 6% decline would have been 9% as the album made up 3.1% of the entire album sales total of 2015.<ref name=\"caulfield1\" />\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Standard edition<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/25/id1051394208|title=iTunes (U.S.) \u2013 Music \u2013 Adele \u2013 25|accessdate=16 November 2015|date=20 November 2015|work=iTunes (U.S.)}}</ref>\n| all_writing = \n| collapsed = no\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title1 = [[Hello (Adele song)|Hello]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Adele Adkins]]|[[Greg Kurstin]]}}\n| extra1 = Kurstin\n| length1 = 4:55\n| title2 = [[Send My Love (To Your New Lover)]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Adkins|[[Max Martin]]|[[Shellback (record producer)|Shellback]]}}\n| extra2 = {{hlist|Martin|Shellback}}\n| length2 = 3:43\n| title3 = I Miss You\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Adkins|[[Paul Epworth]]}}\n| extra3 = Epworth\n| length3 = 5:48\n| title4 = [[When We Were Young (Adele song)|When We Were Young]]\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Adkins|[[Tobias Jesso Jr.]]}}\n| extra4 = [[Ariel Rechtshaid]]\n| length4 = 4:51\n| title5 = Remedy\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Adkins|[[Ryan Tedder]]}}\n| extra5 = Tedder\n| length5 = 4:05\n| title6 = [[Water Under the Bridge (song)|Water Under the Bridge]]\n| writer6 = {{hlist|Adkins|Kurstin}}\n| extra6 = Kurstin\n|